	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories A
man has been killed after he crashed into a cow on the R102 near King Shaka
International Airport on Saturday, paramedics said. IPSS spokesperson Paul Herbst
said the 53-year-old man was killed and his two passengers injured after the
bakkie they were travelling in knocked
into a cow on the southbound lane of the
R102 between the Canelands and airport intersection this morning. "The driver sustained fatal
injuries and was declared dead on the scene by IPSS paramedics, while his wife and
second passenger sustained moderate injuries." Herbst said the cow also died as
a result of the collision. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  